<!--
    Foreground for the adaptive launcher icon: a chunky white block-letter
    "S" centred on the saffron background. Built from five filled
    rectangles (top bar, top-left stem, middle bar, bottom-right stem,
    bottom bar) which Android unions under the default non-zero fill rule
    into one solid silhouette — no strokes, no thin lines, no open paths.

    Layout in the 108-unit logical canvas:
        top bar:        x=28..80  y=26..40   (52 wide, 14 tall)
        top-left stem:  x=28..42  y=26..56
        middle bar:     x=28..80  y=49..63
        bot-right stem: x=66..80  y=52..82
        bottom bar:     x=28..80  y=68..82

    The S spans roughly y=26..82, x=28..80 — about 56 dp tall and 52 dp
    wide, well inside the 66 dp adaptive-icon safe zone (centre 54,54
    radius 33). Even the most aggressive launcher mask (circle / squircle)
    can't crop this and leave the icon looking sparse.
-->
<vector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:width="108dp"
    android:height="108dp"
    android:viewportWidth="108"
    android:viewportHeight="108">
    <path
        android:fillColor="#FFFFFF"
        android:pathData="M28,26 L80,26 L80,40 L28,40 Z M28,26 L42,26 L42,56 L28,56 Z M28,49 L80,49 L80,63 L28,63 Z M66,52 L80,52 L80,82 L66,82 Z M28,68 L80,68 L80,82 L28,82 Z" />
</vector>
